### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

compiler

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

Given a property `foo?: { bar?: number }` in TypeScript, you can write `if (this.foo?.bar)` and the compiler will infer that `this.foo` is not undefined, _and_ that `this.foo.bar` is not undefined either (essentially narrowing the type to `foo: { bar: number }`). This is equivalent to writing `if (this.foo && this.foo.bar)`.

However, the first example doesn't work as expected in Angular templates.

### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug

https://stackblitz.com/edit/kpq3pr?file=src%2Fmain.ts

